Text.LocalizedString: You can find all kinds of things around my house. Oh, like food, I mean!//<portrait=happy>There are wild mushrooms and even fresh fruit sometimes.

Text.SourceString: If you find any wild fruit, feel free to take it, by the way.
Text.LocalizedString: If you find any wild fruit, feel free to take it, by the way.

Text.SourceString: It’s always nice to get together with folks.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s always nice to get together with folks.

Text.SourceString: We’re halfway through Spring already, and I haven’t done my house cleaning yet!
Text.LocalizedString: We’re halfway through Spring already, and I haven’t done my house cleaning yet!

Text.SourceString: Everything is a mess! I can’t even find my old grill.
Text.LocalizedString: Everything is a mess! I can’t even find my old grill.

Text.SourceString: Oh! It’s the last week of Spring already! I really need to find my old grill.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! It’s the last week of Spring already! I really need to find my old grill.

Text.SourceString: You see, this is why we shouldn’t put things away.//Then people can’t see them, and people get irritated when they can’t find what they’re looking for.
Text.LocalizedString: You see, this is why we shouldn’t put things away.//Then people can’t see them, and people get irritated when they can’t find what they’re looking for.

Text.SourceString: Yes. I am, in fact, one of those people.
Text.LocalizedString: Yes. I am, in fact, one of those people.

Text.SourceString: My birthday is on the 13th, and do you know who else has a birthday on the 13th?
Text.LocalizedString: My birthday is on the 13th, and do you know who else has a birthday on the 13th?

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Eva</>! We’ve made it a tradition to exchange gifts every year. It’s a little inside joke. Ha!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Eva</>! We’ve made it a tradition to exchange gifts every year. It’s a little inside joke. Ha!

Text.SourceString: Going to the beach a lot, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Going to the beach a lot, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: We get a lot of bugs here in Summer.//But there must be plenty at the farm too, huh?//<portrait=doubt>I mean, the forest is right there.
Text.LocalizedString: We get a lot of bugs here in Summer.//But there must be plenty at the farm too, huh?//<portrait=doubt>I mean, the forest is right there.

Text.SourceString: But we also get a lot of cosmos, the flowers.//<portrait=normal>So, I don’t want to complain too much about Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: But we also get a lot of cosmos, the flowers.//<portrait=normal>So, I don’t want to complain too much about Summer.

Text.SourceString: I’m out of fish, so I guess I’m only selling vegan tacos tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m out of fish, so I guess I’m only selling vegan tacos tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: No, not a good time. I’ll go shopping for fish next week.//The vegetables will do for now.
Text.LocalizedString: No, not a good time. I’ll go shopping for fish next week.//The vegetables will do for now.

Text.SourceString: Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> has been walking back and forth to town a lot lately.//I guess he’s trying to get things ready for the Harvest Festival.
Text.LocalizedString: Mayor <NPCName>Connor</> has been walking back and forth to town a lot lately.//I guess he’s trying to get things ready for the Harvest Festival.

Text.SourceString: It’s a lot of work being a mayor, you know.//I hardly saw him out fishing all Summer, and he loves fishing.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a lot of work being a mayor, you know.//I hardly saw him out fishing all Summer, and he loves fishing.

Text.SourceString: So lovely to see the Fall festival decorations.//They always do an excellent job.
Text.LocalizedString: So lovely to see the Fall festival decorations.//They always do an excellent job.

Text.SourceString: The whole town looks like a scene from a television show.
Text.LocalizedString: The whole town looks like a scene from a television show.

Text.SourceString: I remember the first Winter I opened my truck.//Almost the whole town showed up to celebrate with me.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember the first Winter I opened my truck.//Almost the whole town showed up to celebrate with me.

Text.SourceString: No, it wasn’t a gathering or anything like that.//<portrait=happy>They came to help out and probably wanted to support my business.
Text.LocalizedString: No, it wasn’t a gathering or anything like that.//<portrait=happy>They came to help out and probably wanted to support my business.

Text.SourceString: I have to forage extra hard during Winter because there’s not much around to begin with.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to forage extra hard during Winter because there’s not much around to begin with.

Text.SourceString: It’s just too cold. Plants can’t survive in the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s just too cold. Plants can’t survive in the snow.

Text.SourceString: With less wild produce available, I have to be very…creative when it comes to my taco recipe.
Text.LocalizedString: With less wild produce available, I have to be very…creative when it comes to my taco recipe.

Text.SourceString: I’ve been using a lot of substitutes lately.//<portrait=normal>I wonder if my customers even notice.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been using a lot of substitutes lately.//<portrait=normal>I wonder if my customers even notice.

Text.SourceString: Isn’t there a saying about snow bringing good luck?
Text.LocalizedString: Isn’t there a saying about snow bringing good luck?

Text.SourceString: Oh, is it the rain? Hmm. Maybe it’s the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, is it the rain? Hmm. Maybe it’s the rain.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Bree’s</> holding an annual appreciation dinner for the mayor.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Bree’s</> holding an annual appreciation dinner for the mayor.

Text.SourceString: It’s great. It’s very nice of her to do that.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s great. It’s very nice of her to do that.

Text.SourceString: I don’t travel in Winter. I’m afraid the truck might get stuck in the middle of a snowstorm.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t travel in Winter. I’m afraid the truck might get stuck in the middle of a snowstorm.

Text.SourceString: I can’t remember the last time I changed the tires, to be perfectly honest. It’s worrisome if you ask me.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t remember the last time I changed the tires, to be perfectly honest. It’s worrisome if you ask me.

Text.SourceString: Please watch your boots. I’d hate to have to mop again.
Text.LocalizedString: Please watch your boots. I’d hate to have to mop again.

Text.SourceString: Wah, the rain is that bad, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Wah, the rain is that bad, huh?

Text.SourceString: I don’t like going out in the rain, so I usually just spend the day cooking.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like going out in the rain, so I usually just spend the day cooking.

Text.SourceString: With this rain, though, tomorrow there may be more wild fruit than usual around the island.
Text.LocalizedString: With this rain, though, tomorrow there may be more wild fruit than usual around the island.

Text.SourceString: Wishful thinking on my part.
Text.LocalizedString: Wishful thinking on my part.

Text.SourceString: I need to crank up the heat in here.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to crank up the heat in here.

Text.SourceString: Please watch your boots. I’d hate to have to mop again.
Text.LocalizedString: Please watch your boots. I’d hate to have to mop again.

Text.SourceString: Wah, the storm is that bad, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Wah, the storm is that bad, huh?

Text.SourceString: I don’t like going out in the rain, so I usually just spend the day cooking.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like going out in the rain, so I usually just spend the day cooking.

Text.SourceString: After the storm, there might be more wild vegetables around the island.//I don’t know for sure, but it’s worth checking!
Text.LocalizedString: After the storm, there might be more wild vegetables around the island.//I don’t know for sure, but it’s worth checking!

Text.SourceString: I’ll have a look tomorrow. Fingers crossed.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll have a look tomorrow. Fingers crossed.

Text.SourceString: I need to crank up the heat in here.
Text.LocalizedString: I need to crank up the heat in here.

Text.SourceString: It feels like it was just snowing yesterday, and now it’s snowing again today.
Text.LocalizedString: It feels like it was just snowing yesterday, and now it’s snowing again today.

Text.SourceString: What luck, eh?

Text.SourceString: Isn’t there a saying about snow bringing good luck?

Text.SourceString: What a great day to be outside.
Text.LocalizedString: What a great day to be outside.

Text.LocalizedString: I think I may take a quick walk later before I head home.//You know, to enjoy the weather.

Text.LocalizedString: You need a really good skillet to make tacos.

Text.LocalizedString: You can use any kind of fish to make fish tacos.//<portrait=happy>Honestly, after I cook the fish, I can’t even taste the difference. It’s all in the seasoning.

Text.LocalizedString: It’s easier than you think to make good vegan tacos.//I personally like bell peppers, but you can use any Summer or Fall vegetables you want.

Text.LocalizedString: When there are no customers, I try to get a quick nap in. Right now, you’re kind of in the way.

Text.SourceString: No offense.
Text.LocalizedString: No offense.

Text.LocalizedString: I have no idea where this creek flows from. But I’m not one for exploring nature, so I can never bring myself to try finding out.

Text.LocalizedString: Heading down to town, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Please watch yourself. Try not to step on anything, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: Please watch yourself. Try not to step on anything, okay?

Text.SourceString: I’m glad you came to visit.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad you came to visit.

Text.SourceString: It’s easier than you think to make good vegan tacos.//I personally like bell peppers, but you can use any Summer or Fall vegetables you want.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s easier than you think to make good vegan tacos.//I personally like bell peppers, but you can use any Summer or Fall vegetables you want.

Text.LocalizedString: Just found some time to do meal prep.//Ah, my hands are so dirty.

Text.SourceString: Might as well marinate some chard for burritos.

Text.LocalizedString: I use red cabbage when it’s in season.//<portrait=happy>It has that nice crunchy texture.

Text.SourceString: It’s good to see you in such good spirits, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s good to see you in such good spirits, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… What else do I need?
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… What else do I need?

Text.SourceString: I just buy my tortillas here. It takes too long to make them from scratch.
Text.LocalizedString: I just buy my tortillas here. It takes too long to make them from scratch.

Text.SourceString: Knowing where this fruit is grown helps me feel more connected to the island.//It also supports local farmers, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Knowing where this fruit is grown helps me feel more connected to the island.//It also supports local farmers, right?

Text.SourceString: I might open my truck later.//<portrait=doubt>I don’t know yet.
Text.LocalizedString: I might open my truck later.//<portrait=doubt>I don’t know yet.

Text.SourceString: It’s easier than you think to make good vegan tacos.//I personally like bell peppers, but you can use any Summer or Fall vegetables you want.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s easier than you think to make good vegan tacos.//I personally like bell peppers, but you can use any Summer or Fall vegetables you want.

Text.SourceString: I use red cabbage when it’s in season.//<portrait=happy>It has that nice crunchy texture.
Text.LocalizedString: I use red cabbage when it’s in season.//<portrait=happy>It has that nice crunchy texture.

Text.SourceString: Hmm. I may need to buy extra flour today.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm. I may need to buy extra flour today.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I should’ve packed an extra lunch.//<portrait=doubt>I ate mine too early, and my stomach is growling again.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I should’ve packed an extra lunch.//<portrait=doubt>I ate mine too early, and my stomach is growling again.

Text.SourceString: Are you on a picnic too?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you on a picnic too?

Text.SourceString: I’m all for trying out something new.//Like painting or sculpting.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m all for trying out something new.//Like painting or sculpting.

Text.SourceString: But, er, don’t expect too much.//<portrait=happy>I love myself enough to admit I don’t have a single artistic bone in my body.
Text.LocalizedString: But, er, don’t expect too much.//<portrait=happy>I love myself enough to admit I don’t have a single artistic bone in my body.

Text.SourceString: I’m so glad I got the cottage when it was cheap.//I think it’s worth twice as much now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so glad I got the cottage when it was cheap.//I think it’s worth twice as much now.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I’ll renovate it one day with enough room for a bigger kitchen, or even a couple of pets!
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I’ll renovate it one day with enough room for a bigger kitchen, or even a couple of pets!

Text.SourceString: Having a big house sounds like a lot of work.//<portrait=normal>It would be nice to have the extra space, but the cleaning and maintenance… Too much commitment.
Text.LocalizedString: Having a big house sounds like a lot of work.//<portrait=normal>It would be nice to have the extra space, but the cleaning and maintenance… Too much commitment.

Text.SourceString: It would be nice to have an extra refrigerator, though.
Text.LocalizedString: It would be nice to have an extra refrigerator, though.

Text.SourceString: I think I’ll go down to Beluga Bay this Summer. Just on weekends.//Spend a day or two, come back Monday.//<portrait=doubt>Can’t go during the week, or I’d lose too much business.
Text.LocalizedString: I think I’ll go down to Beluga Bay this Summer. Just on weekends.//Spend a day or two, come back Monday.//<portrait=doubt>Can’t go during the week, or I’d lose too much business.

Text.SourceString: I have regulars over there.//<portrait=happy>Not a lot, but I appreciate them. Money is money, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I have regulars over there.//<portrait=happy>Not a lot, but I appreciate them. Money is money, right?

Text.SourceString: I try to paint sometimes. *laughs* I’m not good at it!
Text.LocalizedString: I try to paint sometimes. *laughs* I’m not good at it!

Text.SourceString: But who cares, right? I have fun doing it.//<portrait=normal>That’s all that matters.
Text.LocalizedString: But who cares, right? I have fun doing it.//<portrait=normal>That’s all that matters.

Text.SourceString: I liked working at <NPCName>Sam</>’s. I couldn’t bake very well, so the bakery corner had a limited selection back then.//Only bread, if I’m not mistaken. We didn’t even have cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: I liked working at <NPCName>Sam</>’s. I couldn’t bake very well, so the bakery corner had a limited selection back then.//Only bread, if I’m not mistaken. We didn’t even have cookies.

Text.SourceString: I was in charge of stocking and ordering. I was honestly much better at that than at baking.
Text.LocalizedString: I was in charge of stocking and ordering. I was honestly much better at that than at baking.

Text.SourceString: I always knew I didn’t want to stay at <NPCName>Sam</>’s too long.//Not because there were any problems, though.//He was a really good and fair boss.
Text.LocalizedString: I always knew I didn’t want to stay at <NPCName>Sam</>’s too long.//Not because there were any problems, though.//He was a really good and fair boss.

Text.SourceString: I was paid well, but I knew I wanted to cook food, not pastries.//So I saved up my salary until I could afford a used truck and my own cottage.//<portrait=happy>And I did.
Text.LocalizedString: I was paid well, but I knew I wanted to cook food, not pastries.//So I saved up my salary until I could afford a used truck and my own cottage.//<portrait=happy>And I did.

Text.SourceString: When I think about it, I owe my independence to <NPCName>Sam</> and <NPCName>Emily</>, in a way.//I could’ve worked at Sockets or at the clinic, and I would have worked just as hard.
Text.LocalizedString: When I think about it, I owe my independence to <NPCName>Sam</> and <NPCName>Emily</>, in a way.//I could’ve worked at Sockets or at the clinic, and I would have worked just as hard.

Text.SourceString: But I’m thankful they took me under their wing. And for the memories too.//I owe <NPCName>Sam</> and <NPCName>Emily</> for a lot of good memories and life lessons.//<portrait=normal>They were very encouraging and supportive.
Text.LocalizedString: But I’m thankful they took me under their wing. And for the memories too.//I owe <NPCName>Sam</> and <NPCName>Emily</> for a lot of good memories and life lessons.//<portrait=normal>They were very encouraging and supportive.

Text.SourceString: I should probably visit <NPCName>Sam</> and <NPCName>Emily</> one of these days. Catch up and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: I should probably visit <NPCName>Sam</> and <NPCName>Emily</> one of these days. Catch up and stuff.

Text.SourceString: I know they like having visitors, especially <NPCName>Emily</>.//<portrait=concerned>She always complains about the house being too quiet.
Text.LocalizedString: I know they like having visitors, especially <NPCName>Emily</>.//<portrait=concerned>She always complains about the house being too quiet.

Text.SourceString: I know it isn’t a lot, but I’m proud of myself for getting this food truck.//<portrait=happy>A little pat on my own back. Self-love. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I know it isn’t a lot, but I’m proud of myself for getting this food truck.//<portrait=happy>A little pat on my own back. Self-love. Ha ha!

Text.SourceString: The food truck business can be tricky. I had to go back and forth between here and Beluga Bay a lot in the beginning.//I was trying to build up a customer base.
Text.LocalizedString: The food truck business can be tricky. I had to go back and forth between here and Beluga Bay a lot in the beginning.//I was trying to build up a customer base.

Text.SourceString: Traveling takes its toll. Now I’m too tired to do it regularly.//Thankfully, I do just fine focusing my business here in Starlet Town.
Text.LocalizedString: Traveling takes its toll. Now I’m too tired to do it regularly.//Thankfully, I do just fine focusing my business here in Starlet Town.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to treat myself to some hot cocoa later. Yum. That sounds so good!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to treat myself to some hot cocoa later. Yum. That sounds so good!

Text.SourceString: My favorite food would be tacos, obviously. I like pumpkin too.//<portrait=doubt>Come to think of it, there isn’t any food I hate.//<portrait=annoyed>Wow! That shocks <Italic>me</>.
Text.LocalizedString: My favorite food would be tacos, obviously. I like pumpkin too.//<portrait=doubt>Come to think of it, there isn’t any food I hate.//<portrait=annoyed>Wow! That shocks <Italic>me</>.

Text.SourceString: I’d pretty much eat anything.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d pretty much eat anything.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Sam</> gave me my first grocery orders for free. He told me to just pay when I could.//It really helped in the beginning when I was just starting my food truck business.//<portrait=happy>I’ll never forget that.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Sam</> gave me my first grocery orders for free. He told me to just pay when I could.//It really helped in the beginning when I was just starting my food truck business.//<portrait=happy>I’ll never forget that.

Text.SourceString: You shop here too?
Text.LocalizedString: You shop here too?

Text.SourceString: I used to work over there, by the oven.//It wasn’t as big back in the day.
Text.LocalizedString: I used to work over there, by the oven.//It wasn’t as big back in the day.

Text.SourceString: They need the big oven now. With <NPCName>Eva’s</> great baking skills, they can make so much more stuff. Faster too.
Text.LocalizedString: They need the big oven now. With <NPCName>Eva’s</> great baking skills, they can make so much more stuff. Faster too.

Text.SourceString: I ate moldy bread one time, and I was sick for two days. Never again!//<portrait=happy>Hey, I like how we’re opening up to each other!
Text.LocalizedString: I ate moldy bread one time, and I was sick for two days. Never again!//<portrait=happy>Hey, I like how we’re opening up to each other!

Text.SourceString: Here’s an insider tip: <NPCName>Dippa</> hates fresh tomatoes.//You know, I could never understand that. Fresh tomatoes taste fine to me.//I don’t love them, but hate? Nah.
Text.LocalizedString: Here’s an insider tip: <NPCName>Dippa</> hates fresh tomatoes.//You know, I could never understand that. Fresh tomatoes taste fine to me.//I don’t love them, but hate? Nah.

Text.SourceString: That reminds me. I need to get some flour and tortillas.
Text.LocalizedString: That reminds me. I need to get some flour and tortillas.

Text.SourceString: You look like the type who enjoys afternoon tea with cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: You look like the type who enjoys afternoon tea with cookies.

Text.SourceString: True. Look at us. Getting to know each other!
Text.LocalizedString: True. Look at us. Getting to know each other!

Text.SourceString: I knew it! I love getting to know new people.
Text.LocalizedString: I knew it! I love getting to know new people.

Text.SourceString: Aww. All right. Well, the more you know!
Text.LocalizedString: Aww. All right. Well, the more you know!

Text.SourceString: How are things going, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: How are things going, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Enjoy the cherry blossom festival! I'm skipping it to take care of my garden.//No energy for anything else.
Text.LocalizedString: Enjoy the cherry blossom festival! I'm skipping it to take care of my garden.//No energy for anything else.

Text.SourceString: We planted plenty of potatoes in our garden.//I might start adding them to my tacos. Use them for a crispy topping.//<portrait=happy>The kids might like that.
Text.LocalizedString: We planted plenty of potatoes in our garden.//I might start adding them to my tacos. Use them for a crispy topping.//<portrait=happy>The kids might like that.

Text.SourceString: Don’t let the warm weather make you lazy.//I try to do a set of jumping jacks every morning before starting my day.//<portrait=happy>Get my blood pumping!
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t let the warm weather make you lazy.//I try to do a set of jumping jacks every morning before starting my day.//<portrait=happy>Get my blood pumping!

Text.SourceString: Homegrown tomatoes make all the difference in tacos.//They’re fresh, and more importantly, cheap!
Text.LocalizedString: Homegrown tomatoes make all the difference in tacos.//They’re fresh, and more importantly, cheap!

Text.SourceString: It’s much cheaper to grow food than to buy it at <NPCName>Sam</>’s.//<portrait=happy>Not swimming in money over here.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s much cheaper to grow food than to buy it at <NPCName>Sam</>’s.//<portrait=happy>Not swimming in money over here.

Text.SourceString: This year’s corn is so sweet.//It’s a great crop!
Text.LocalizedString: This year’s corn is so sweet.//It’s a great crop!

Text.SourceString: We’ve lost a lot of crops lately.//<portrait=happy>I think there’s a wombat out there with a taste for sweet potatoes.
Text.LocalizedString: We’ve lost a lot of crops lately.//<portrait=happy>I think there’s a wombat out there with a taste for sweet potatoes.

Text.SourceString: I enjoy my walk to work.//The cooler weather is refreshing.
Text.LocalizedString: I enjoy my walk to work.//The cooler weather is refreshing.

Text.SourceString: I keep a portable heater in my truck.//It’s pretty small, but it works well. I got it at Socket & Pan.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep a portable heater in my truck.//It’s pretty small, but it works well. I got it at Socket & Pan.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Dippa</> has some paintings at Socket & Pan, so <NpcName>Luke</> gives us a discount.//<portrait=happy>Money, money, money!
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Dippa</> has some paintings at Socket & Pan, so <NpcName>Luke</> gives us a discount.//<portrait=happy>Money, money, money!

Text.SourceString: I remember when money used to be tight, tighter than now.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Dippa</> and I went shopping for our first dining table. My old one was a side table.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember when money used to be tight, tighter than now.//<portrait=happy><NpcName>Dippa</> and I went shopping for our first dining table. My old one was a side table.

Text.SourceString: We saw this beautiful pair of floral sofas.//We couldn’t afford the set, so <NpcName>Joko</> sold us just one.//The next time we went back, the other one was gone. Too bad!
Text.LocalizedString: We saw this beautiful pair of floral sofas.//We couldn’t afford the set, so <NpcName>Joko</> sold us just one.//The next time we went back, the other one was gone. Too bad!

Text.SourceString: What’s up, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s up, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: Sure! It’s super comfy.//<portrait=doubt>I got it from <NpcName>Ben</>. I sent him the bill from his tab at the truck, and instead of money, he paid it with the hammock.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure! It’s super comfy.//<portrait=doubt>I got it from <NpcName>Ben</>. I sent him the bill from his tab at the truck, and instead of money, he paid it with the hammock.

Special.SourceString: Can I nap in your hammock?
Special.LocalizedString: Can I nap in your hammock?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Ben</>. He had a long overdue tab at the truck and decided to pay with a hammock.//<portrait=happy>It’s super comfy.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Ben</>. He had a long overdue tab at the truck and decided to pay with a hammock.//<portrait=happy>It’s super comfy.

Special.SourceString: Where did you get your hammock?
Special.LocalizedString: Where did you get your hammock?

Text.SourceString: Umm, no. We have wombats doing that already.//<portrait=happy>But if you’re hungry, I can send you some food.
Text.LocalizedString: Umm, no. We have wombats doing that already.//<portrait=happy>But if you’re hungry, I can send you some food.

Special.SourceString: Can I pick something from your garden?
Special.LocalizedString: Can I pick something from your garden?

Text.SourceString: I don’t recommend wearing sandals to walk in the woods.//Broke mine the other day. I had to walk home barefoot. The path was scorching hot!
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t recommend wearing sandals to walk in the woods.//Broke mine the other day. I had to walk home barefoot. The path was scorching hot!

Text.SourceString: I got my sandals from <NpcName>Ben</>.//<portrait=normal>I’ll stick to shoes from now on.
Text.LocalizedString: I got my sandals from <NpcName>Ben</>.//<portrait=normal>I’ll stick to shoes from now on.

Text.SourceString: Gonna check out <NpcName>Ben’s</> stuff this weekend.//He usually brings back some interesting things from his trips.
Text.LocalizedString: Gonna check out <NpcName>Ben’s</> stuff this weekend.//He usually brings back some interesting things from his trips.

Text.SourceString: Besides, he’s got some bills to pay.//<portrait=happy>Maybe he can just pay with seeds or new blankets.
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, he’s got some bills to pay.//<portrait=happy>Maybe he can just pay with seeds or new blankets.

Text.SourceString: The mayor has the best hats.//I saw him walking around with a cactus on his hat.//<portrait=happy>He’s so cool!
Text.LocalizedString: The mayor has the best hats.//I saw him walking around with a cactus on his hat.//<portrait=happy>He’s so cool!

Text.SourceString: How much do you think it would cost to install a little television in my truck?//<portrait=doubt>It would be a nice way to pass the time.
Text.LocalizedString: How much do you think it would cost to install a little television in my truck?//<portrait=doubt>It would be a nice way to pass the time.

Text.SourceString: It’d be nice to have an automatic window in the roof.//The kind that you press a button to open. Must be expensive to install, though.
Text.LocalizedString: It’d be nice to have an automatic window in the roof.//The kind that you press a button to open. Must be expensive to install, though.

Text.SourceString: Press a button, breeze comes in. Whoosh!//Press a button, quiet.
Text.LocalizedString: Press a button, breeze comes in. Whoosh!//Press a button, quiet.
